## 🐛 Bug Report

Implementation of cell.fill.fgColor with black text is displaying appropriate colors in GoogleSheets, but showing black fill/white text on Libre, and black fill/black text in Excel.

Lib version: 4.3.0

## Steps To Reproduce

```
//startCell has been already merged with all necessary relevant cells up to this point;

startCell.value = team.name +"\n" + timeConverterExpress.runConvertTotalMinutesToTime(trainingDay.startTime) +" :\n " + timeConverterExpress.runConvertTotalMinutesToTime(trainingDay.endTime);
startCell.alignment = {vertical: "middle", horizontal: "center", wrapText: true};
startCell.border = {top: {style:'medium'}, left: {style:'medium'}, bottom: {style:'medium'}, right: {style:'medium'}}
startCell.font = { name: 'Calibri', size: 11 }
startCell.fill = {type: "pattern", pattern: "solid", fgColor: {argb: team.color}};

// appropriate team.color is working in GoogleSheets, but not Libre or Excel
//order or existence of assigning other style properties do not seem to have any bearing on output
```

## The expected behaviour:

Cell fill colors should work similarly throughout Excel/Libre/GoogleSheets 

